To use this module:

ImageMagick must be installed. Use the `download-packages` utility in a terminal to download the necessary packages for persistent use:

`download-packages imagemagick`

Verify the packages are downloaded into /ARCOS-DATA/QRV/.packages/packages-XXXXX.

The packages required are:
imagemagick-6-common imagemagick-6.q16 libjxr-tools libjxr0t64 liblqr-1-0 libmagickcore-6.q16-7-extra libmagickcore-6.q16-7t64 libmagickwand-6.q16-7t64 libnetpbm11t64 netpbm

1) Place the BAND-CONDITIONS-CONKY directory in the USER Module directory:
     - /ARCOS-DATA/QRV/CALLSIGN/arcos-linux-modules/USER

2) Place the 05_BAND-CONDITIONS-CONKY.sh script in the USER Module directory, as well.
     - One level up from where it is now.

Notes:
The module will be active on the next reboot or re-run of Station Setup.

To deactivate the module, place the 05_BAND-CONDITIONS-CONKY.sh script back inside the BAND-CONDITIONS-CONKY directory and reboot.
